text:
East River, Queens shore, at Whitestone Landing, showing the shore as seen from the Boerum boat house, looking east. On the extreme right is a portion of Stimmel's Pavilion, at the foot of Bayside Avenue, later 152nd Street. Stimmel's later became Beckmann's Pavilion. The pavilion bears the sign N.Y. Herald.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
May, 1898
title: East River - Queens shore - Whitestone Landing.
